The `scroll-snap-type` and `scroll-snap-align` properties can be used to detect the end of a scroll event. These properties control the snapping behavior of an element when it is scrolled. By setting them to `mandatory`, the browser will snap the element to a specific position when the user finishes scrolling it. You can use the `scroll-snap-type` and `scroll-snap-align` properties to detect the end of a scroll event, as the browser will snap the element to a specific position when the user finishes scrolling it.

